<FIRST>d a PM-BRF--Abortion-Arson     09-07 0132</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Abortion-Arson,0138</SECOND>
<HEAD>Clinic's New Home Burns</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PITTSBURGH (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An arson fire caused $5,000 damage to an
abortion clinic that had moved in the hope of escaping further
attention of abortion protesters, authorities said.
   Flammable liquid was thrown against the Allegheny Reproductive
Health Center entrance early Wednesday, then was ignited, said
Deputy Fire Chief John Harper.
   The fire damaged the door, a staircase and an awning, Harper said.
   No arrests were made.
   The building was unoccupied when the fire broke out, said
executive director Claire Keyes.
   ``We're very thankful that there were no injuries when this
terroristic act occurred,'' she said. ``We want to assure our
patients that services will be continuing uninterrupted.''
   During the weekend, the clinic moved from a building across the
street, where several protests had been staged.
</TEXT>
