<FIRST>d a PM-BRF--TextbookRobbery     09-07 0159</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Textbook Robbery,0163</SECOND>
<HEAD>Police on Way to Robbery Seminar Nab Robbery Suspect</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PLANTATION, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two police officers on their way to an
armed robbery seminar noticed a man walking down the street with
money sticking out of his pockets.
   Detective Larry Massey remarked, ``If I were on road patrol, that
would be someone I would pull over.''
   That's when a call came over the police radio Wednesday about a
$2,000 armed robbery 10 minutes earlier at an NCNB bank branch a
half-mile away.
   Massey and Officer William Martin stopped the pedestrian, Brendan
Vincent Masterson, 19, of Carol City, and drove him to the bank,
where a teller identified him as the robber.
   In addition to the cash in his pockets, Masterson was carrying
three notes that said, ``Freeze, I have a bomb. Give me all your
cash,'' police said.
   Masterson was charged with armed robbery and was being held
without bail in the Broward County Jail.
</TEXT>
