<FIRST>r a PM-MTVAwards-Clay     09-07 0222</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-MTV Awards-Clay,0229</SECOND>
<HEAD>Comedian Andrew Dice Clay Kicked Off MTV</HEAD>
<DATELINE>UNIVERSAL CITY, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Comic Andrew Dice Clay was booted
off the MTV cable network after delivering a monologue laced with
lewd poetry and references to obese women and sex.
   As the MTV Video Music Awards show continued Wednesday night
shortly after Clay's segment, MTV Vice President Barry Kluger came
backstage and read to reporters a network statement expressing
``extreme regret'' for Clay's performance.
   ``As you know, our show is a live performance and we had
assurances, repeatedly, that his material would be in line with our
programming standards, which naturally preclude profanity and
obscenity,'' Kluger said.
   ``MTV apologizes for his breach of his agreement with us and we
apologize to our viewers.
   ``Andrew Dice Clay did not do this in rehearsal and we were very
surprised by it. Based on this experience, Andrew Dice Clay will not
be appearing on MTV in the future,'' Kluger said.
   The comedian had stopped by the press area immediately after his
routine and answered questions in a brief session in which he stayed
in his stage character of an arrogant chauvinist.
   He left before Kluger arrived backstage with the MTV reaction.
   Kluger would answer no questions.
   Clay's brash style caused a record company to put a warning label
on his live album, ``Dice.''
</TEXT>
