<SECOND>PM-MTV Awards-List,0204</SECOND>
<HEAD>Winners of MTV Awards</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is a list of winners for the MTV Video
Music Awards, presented Wednesday night.
   Video: Neil Young for ``This Note's for You.''
   Group: Living Colour for ``Cult of Personality.''
   Male: Elvis Costello for ``Veronica.''
   Female: Abdul for ``Straight Up.''
   New Artist: Living Colour for ``Cult of Personality.''
   Heavy Metal: Guns 'N Roses for ``Sweet Child O' Mine.''
   Rap: DJ Jazzy Jeff &amp; The Fresh Prince for ``Parents Just Don't
Understand.''
   Dance: Paula Abdul for ``Straight Up.''
   Film: U2 With B.B. King for ``When Loves Comes to Town'' from
``Rattle and Hum.''
   Choreography: Abdul for ``Straight Up.''
   Stage: Living Colour for ``Cult of Personality.''
   Direction: Madonna (director David Fincher) for ``Express
Yourself.''
   Video Vanguard Award: George Michael.
   Editing: Abdul (editor Jim Heygood) for ``Straight Up.''
   Post Modern: R.E.M. for ``Orange Crush.''
   Special Effects: Michael Jackson (special effects Jim Blashfield)
for ``Leave Me Alone.''
   Art Direction: Madonna (director Vance Lorenzini) for ``Express
Yourself.''
   Cinematography: Madonna (cinematographer Mark Plummer) for
``Express Yourself.''
   Breakthrough Video: Art of Noise for ``Kiss.''
   Viewers Choice: Madonna, ``Like A Prayer.''
