<SECOND>AM-Gang Rape,0317</SECOND>
<HEAD>Nine Men and Women Suspected in Sex Assault on Pregnant Woman</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By MARIO FOX</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A pregnant woman was abducted off the street,
taken to an apartment and sexually assaulted by nine men and women
for six hours, police said Thursday.
   The attackers also beat and tore clumps of hair out of the
25-year-old victim, who is seven months pregnant, said Officer Clyde
Brandenburger. He said they used no weapons.
   The victim was treated for bruises at Jackson Park Hospital and
released, said nursing supervisor Edna Sistrunk. She said she
couldn't comment on the status of the pregnancy, but Detective Ray
McNally said he believes the fetus survived.
   ``She says she was raped six or seven times and forced to perform
other sexual acts during six hours,'' McNally said. ``This has
happened before, but never with so many people involved.''
   Three suspects _ William Patterson, 31, Courtney Hicks, 36, and
Diane Daniels, 30, all of Chicago _ were arrested and charged with
aggravated criminal sexual assault, McNally said. Police were
seeking six other people, three men and three women.
   Investigators don't believe illegal drugs were involved, McNally
said.
   The victim had been a few miles from her home, visiting her
sister, when two men grabbed her and dragged her into a nearby
apartment where Patterson lives, McNally said. He said she
apparently didn't know any of her attackers.
   After being repeatedly attacked, the victim was able to sneak
from the bathroom to a back door and escaped from a rear window of
the house, McNally said.
   The nude woman flagged down a police car and led officers to the
apartment, where the three suspects were taken into custody, he said.
   Police recovered her clothes at the scene, and about $30 in cash
she said had been stolen from her.
