<FIRST>r i AM-CathedralPlunge     09-07 0205</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Cathedral Plunge,0211</SECOND>
<HEAD>Man Plunges To Death At St. Paul's Cathedral</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man climbed over a safety barrier inside the dome
of St. Paul's Cathedral and leapt 105 feet to his death Thursday, a
witness said.
   The cathedral was filled with tourists, when the unidentified man
plummeted from the dome's Whispering Gallery onto metal folding
chairs.
   French student Jacques Peyrou, who saw it, said there was no time
for anyone to act.
   Peyrou, 23, from Paris, said he was standing about 15 feet from
the man, who he said was about 50 years old.
   ``I looked up and I could see a man climbing over the barrier.
Very quickly he then leapt over. There was no chance for anyone to
grab him or stop him.''
   Several fatal falls have occurred from the gallery and safety
barriers were built after one such incident in the 19th century. The
last previous fatality came in the 1920s, according to the dean of
St. Paul's, the Very Rev. Eric Evans.
   The round Whispering Gallery is a special attraction at the
cathedral _ Sir Chrisopher Wren's 17th-century masterpiece. Sound is
reflected off the walls and a whisper can be heard clearly more than
100 feet away.
</TEXT>
