hangs on the interpretation of confusing capital standards adopted
by Congress last month, regulators said.
   The key reform in the bill requires S&amp;L owners to risk more of
their own capital as a buffer between losses and government deposit
insurance funds.
   However, S&amp;L regulators said Wednesday they are not sure exactly
how tough the standard should be. The problem is the final bill was
cobbled together from very different versions passed separately by
the House and Senate, they said.
</TEXT>
