21.4 percent in late August over last year as customers took
advantage of end-of-the-model-year sales and looming price increases.
   For the entire month, with import sales included, car and truck
sales rose 8.4 percent compared with August of last year, automakers
said Wednesday. Domestic vehicles showed a significant gain.
   Vehicles made by the eight automakers with U.S. plants sold at an
