<SECOND>PM-AT&amp;T Contract,0175</SECOND>
<HEAD>AT&amp;T Wins Two Contracts</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   American Telephone &amp; Telegraph Co. won two
contracts worth $45 million to provide hotel communications
equipment and toll-free reservation service to Quality Inns
International, AT&amp;T said.
   Quality's reservations network will use AT&amp;T Megacom and Megacom
800 service for toll-free incoming and outgoing calls under terms of
a multiyear agreement estimated at $33 million, AT&amp;T said Wednesday.
   AT&amp;T also won a $12 million contract to provide each of Quality's
new line of budget hotels, called Sleep Inns, with a digital
communications system that will include automatic wakeup calling,
room-maid service and check-in and check-out service.
   On Tuesday, AT&amp;T announced it had won a five-year, $50 million
contract from PaineWebber to provide custom, digital voice and data
service for the security firm's 270 offices nationwide.
   AT&amp;T on Tuesday also said Kemper Financial Services Cos. had
agreed to a five-year, $50 million contract for a custom voice and
data network to link 180 of Kemper's investment management and
financial services offices.
