<FIRST>r f BC-EEC-Unemployment     09-07 0209</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-EEC-Unemployment,0217</SECOND>
<HEAD>EEC Jobless Rate 9.3 Percent In July, Same as June</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BRUSSELS, Belgium (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The European Economic Community's
average jobless rate was 9.3 percent in July, unchanged from the
previous three months and 0.1 points below the rates of January and
February, the EEC statistics agency Eurostat said Thursday.
   ``In the six months to July 1989, the unemployment rate for the
Community as a whole has remained stable,'' Eurostat reported.
   ``Falls in Spain (-1.3 percent), the United Kingdon (-0.6
percent) and Ireland (-0.3 percent) have been offset by rises in
Denmark (0.6 percent) and Italy (0.3 percent) while the rates in all
other member states have remained broadly unchanged.''
   Eurostat said the jobless rates have stabilized for both men and
women at 7.3 and 12.2 percent respectively.
   It gave no figure for the total number of jobless in July,
because of a new calculating method used in the Netherlands. The
figure for June was 14.1 million.
   Eurostat reported these unemployment rates for each EEC state at
the end of July: Belgium, 9.7 percent; Denmark, 7.3 percent; West
Germany, 5.8 percent; Spain, 17 percent; France, 10.1 percent;
Ireland, 17.1 percent; Italy, 10.9 percent; Luxembourg, 2 percent;
Netherlands, 10 percent; Portugal, 5.6 percent and Great Britain,
6.7 percent.
</TEXT>
