<FIRST>r f BC-CoalProdn     09-07 0103</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Coal Prodn,0108</SECOND>
<HEAD>Industry Reports Weekly Production</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: Only version planned.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Domestic coal production totaled 20 million
short tons during the week ending Aug. 26, up slightly from the 19.9
million short tons produced in the previous week, the Department of
Energy reported Thursday.
   The U.S. coal industry produced 19.7 million short tons in the
same week last year, according to the department's Energy
Information Administration.
   Domestic coal production so far this year is 622.3 million short
tons, 3 percent above last year's production at this time, the
agency said.
   The week's production accounts for bituminous and lignite coal.
</TEXT>
