<FIRST>u f BC-Britain-Stocks 1stLd-Writethru f0020 09-07 0178</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Britain-Stocks, 1st Ld-Writethru, f0020,0184</SECOND>
<HEAD>London Shares Stage Reversal, Close Sharply Higher</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: New thruout with closing prices.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Share prices closed sharply higher Thursday on
London's stock exchange, recovering some lost ground in modest
dealings after interest-rate fears abated.
   The FT-SE 100-share index closed at 2,415.9, up 25.1 points, or
1.04 percent. The key index had lost 35.2 points Wednesday.
   A narrower measure of the market, the FT-SE 30-share index, rose
19.8 to 1,998.5. The FT 500 share index rose 12.20 points to
1,350.25.
   Volume was modest at 508.9 million shares, down from 540.1
million Wednesday.
   Dealers said they saw the recovery largely as a reaction to the
severity of Wednesday's drop.
   Dealers said there have been growing concerns over whether
institutional players will aggressively buy anew, or just seek to
book profits before the end of the third quarter.
   ``It feels good enough at the moment,'' a British dealer said of
the FT-SE 100's return to levels above 2,400. ``It could go further.
But a lot depends on what Wall Street does overnight.''
</TEXT>
