<FIRST>r f AM-Grace-Brzezinski     09-07 0183</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Grace-Brzezinski,0190</SECOND>
<HEAD>W.R. Grace Names Former National Security Advisor To Board</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   W.R. Grace &amp; Co. has named former National
Security Advisor Zbigniew Brzezinski to its board of directors, the
company said Thursday.
   Brzezinski, a professor at Johns Hopkins University, served as
security advisor to President Jimmy Carter from 1977 to 1981.
   ``With more than one-third of Grace's business conducted outside
the U.S., Dr. Brzezinski's addition to the board will provide the
company with access to his vast international expertise,'' said J.
Peter Grace, company chairman and chief executive.
   ``As one of the few U.S. companies with a wholly-owned operation
in China, as well as a developing business with the Soviet Union and
other parts of the world, Dr. Brzezinski's counsel will provide an
intimate view and perspective to world affairs,'' he said.
   Brzezinski, 61, has served on the faculties of Harvard University
and Columbia University. He currently is a counselor at the Center
for Strategic and International Studies.
   W.R. Grace, based in New York, is an international specialty
chemical company with interests in energy, manufacturing and service
businesses.
