<FIRST>r f BC-Armco     09-07 0184</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Armco,0191</SECOND>
<HEAD>Armco Agreement Ratified</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PITTSBURGH (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Members of the United Steelworkers union
ratified a new four-year agreement with Armco Inc., the union said
Thursday.
   The agreement covers 4,700 Armco workers at plants in Ashland,
Ky., Kansas City, Mo., and Baltimore, Md. It was approved by a mail
ballot vote of 3,011 to 685, the union said.
   ``This is an outstanding agreement consistent with the pattern
established at other major steel producers that restores past
sacrifices, assures future economic improvements and develops new
programs for training,'' said Jim Bowen, chairman of the USW
bargaining committee.
   Highlights of the agreement, which runs through July 31, 1993,
include a $500 signing bonus, a profit-sharing plan and immediate
restoration of past wage sacrifices that averaged $1 an hour at the
Baltimore and Kansas City plants.
   The agreement also features wage increases at Baltimore and
Kansas City averaging 35 cents an hour on Aug. 1, 1991, and 40 cents
an hour a year later. Ashland workers will receive average increases
of $1 an hour on Jan. 1, 1991, and 25 cents each of the following
years.
</TEXT>
